<br />
<br />1) Using boards for social interaction (not bad in itself, just doesn't mix well with focused technical discussion)
<br />2) Switching topics when something becomes difficult
<br />3) Lack of serious technical atmosphere in the first place
<br />
<br />Fortunately the <a href="http://nesdev.com/wiki/?page=NesDevWiki" class="postlink">NesDevWiki</a> serves as the host for the most serious technical efforts.

		

